</ast>

<description>

The Manage Scheduler Jobs page displays a table of all batch jobs with columns for Job Name, Is Active (toggle), CRON Expression, Previous Run Status (Success/Failed with start/end times), Next Run Time, Currently Running indicator, and action buttons. Jobs include Apply Annual Fee, Add Accrual Transactions, Apply Penalty to Overdue Loans, Update Loan Summary, Post Interest for Savings, Transfer Fees, and Generate Loan Loss Provisioning. Each job can be toggled active/inactive and its CRON expression edited. A global Start/Stop scheduler toggle controls whether all scheduled jobs execute.

The Global Configuration page displays a table of system-wide feature flags with columns for Configuration Name, Enabled (toggle), Value, and Description. Key settings include maker-checker (4-eyes approval), reschedule-future-repayments, allow-transactions-on-non-workingday, reschedule-repayments-on-holidays, savings-interest-posting-current-period-end, financial-year-beginning-month, and meetings-mandatory-for-jlg-loans.

The Manage Codes page lists all code lists (Client Type, Gender, Address Type, Loan Purpose, etc.) with Name and Is System Defined columns. Clicking a code opens its values for adding, editing, reordering, and deactivating entries that populate dropdown options throughout the system.

The Manage Data Tables page lists custom data tables that extend core entities (m_client, m_group, m_loan, m_office, m_saving_account, m_product_loan, m_savings_product) with custom fields. The Create form includes Data Table Name, Application Table Name dropdown, Multi Row checkbox, and column definitions — each with Name, Type (string, number, boolean, decimal, date, datetime, text, dropdown), Length, Is Mandatory, and Is Unique checkboxes.

The Audit Trails page displays all system actions with columns for Action Name, Entity Name, Resource ID, Maker, Made On Date, Checker, Checked On Date, Processing Result (Pending, Approved, Rejected), Office Name, and Client/Loan/Savings details. Filters allow searching by Action Name, Entity Name, Resource ID, Maker ID, Checker ID, Office, and Date Range. When maker-checker is enabled, pending commands appear with Approve and Reject buttons.

---


</description>

<workflows>
WF-001 | Toggle global scheduler Start/Stop | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Scheduler_Enabled | on_success: toggles scheduler start/stop for all scheduled jobs
WF-002 | Toggle a scheduler job active/inactive | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Is_Active | on_success: toggles job active state
WF-003 | Edit job CRON expression (inline field) | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: CRON_Expression | on_success: updates job CRON expression
WF-004 | Edit job CRON expression (Edit_CRON row action) | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Edit_CRON | on_success: updates job CRON expression
WF-005 | Toggle configuration Enabled (inline) | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Enabled | on_success: toggles configuration enabled state
WF-006 | Update configuration Value (inline) | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Value | on_success: updates configuration value
WF-007 | Edit configuration (row action) | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Edit_Configuration | on_success: updates configuration
WF-008 | Open a code list's values | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Open_Code_Values | on_success: opens Code Values editor for the selected code
WF-009 | Add a new code value | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Add_Value | on_success: adds new code value entry
WF-010 | Edit a code value entry | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Edit_Value | on_success: updates code value entry
WF-011 | Deactivate a code value entry | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Deactivate_Value | on_success: marks code value as inactive
WF-012 | Move a code value up in ordering | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Move_Up | on_success: moves entry up in ordering
WF-013 | Move a code value down in ordering | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Move_Down | on_success: moves entry down in ordering
WF-014 | Create Data Table action (opens form) | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Create_Data_Table | on_success: creates custom data table
WF-015 | Edit a custom data table (row action) | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Edit_Data_Table | on_success: opens data table definition editor
WF-016 | Delete a custom data table (requires confirmation) | actor: <role> | branch: user must confirm deletion | terminal: Delete_Data_Table | on_success: deletes custom data table
WF-017 | Submit Create Data Table form (Create) | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Create | on_success: creates data table definition
WF-018 | Cancel Create Data Table form | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Cancel | on_success: closes form without creating
WF-019 | Approve an Audit Trail entry | actor: <role> | branch: maker-checker enabled AND Processing Result == Pending | terminal: Approve | on_success: sets Processing Result to Approved
WF-020 | Reject an Audit Trail entry | actor: <role> | branch: maker-checker enabled AND Processing Result == Pending | terminal: Reject | on_success: sets Processing Result to Rejected
</workflows>

